{{Taxobox | name = | image = K. marmoratus Guadeloupe.jpg | image_caption = [[Mangrove rivulus]] (''K. marmoratus'') | regnum = [[Animalia]] | phylum = [[Chordata]] | classis = [[Actinopterygii]] | ordo = [[Cyprinodontiformes]] | familia = [[Aplocheilidae]] | genus = '''''Kryptolebias''''' | genus_authority = [[Wilson José Eduardo Moreira da Costa|W. J. E. M. Costa]], 2004 }}
'''''Kryptolebias''''' is a [[genus]] of [[fish]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Aplocheilidae]] mostly native to warm parts of South America but with one species (''K. marmoratus'') found north through the Caribbean region to the [[Gulf Coast of the United States|Gulf Coast states of the United States]]. They are small fish, up to {{cvt|7.5|cm}} in [[total length]].<ref name=FishBase>{{FishBase genus | genus = Kryptolebias| month = October | year = 2018}}</ref> They are non-annual [[killifish]].<ref name=Berois2015>{{cite book | editor1=Berois, N. | editor2=G. García | editor3=R.O. de Sá | year=2015 | title=Annual Fishes: Life History Strategy, Diversity, and Evolution | page=16 | publisher=CRC Press | isbn=9781482299717 }}</ref>
==Species== [[File:Kryptolebias ocellatus.jpeg|thumb|''K. ocellatus'']]
There are currently 8 recognized species in this genus:<ref name=FishBase/>
* ''[[Kryptolebias brasiliensis]]'' <small>[[Achille Valenciennes|Valenciennes]], 1821</small> * ''[[Kryptolebias campelloi]]'' <small>[[Wilson José Eduardo Moreira da Costa|W. J. E. M. Costa]], 1990</small> * ''[[Kryptolebias caudomarginatus]]'' <small>[[Lothar Seegers|Seegers]], 1984</small> * ''[[Kryptolebias gracilis]]'' <small>[[Wilson José Eduardo Moreira da Costa|W. J. E. M. Costa]], 2007</small> * ''[[Kryptolebias hermaphroditus]]'' <small>[[Wilson José Eduardo Moreira da Costa|W. J. E. M. Costa]], 2011</small> * ''[[Kryptolebias marmoratus]]'' <small>[[Felipe Poey y Aloy|Poey]], 1880</small> (Mangrove rivulus) * ''[[Kryptolebias ocellatus]]'' <small>[[Reinhold Friedrich Hensel|R. F. Hensel]], 1868</small> * ''[[Kryptolebias sepia]]'' <small>[[Frans B. M. Vermeulen|Vermeulen]] & [[Tomas Hrbek|Hrbek]], 2005</small>
