{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}

The '''Lems''' was an English [[electric car]] manufactured by the London Electromobile Syndicate in London from 1903 to 1904.  The two-seater [[Runabout (car)|runabout]] claimed to run {{convert|40|mi|km}} on a single charge and reach a top speed of 12&nbsp;mph (19&nbsp;km/h). It was sold for 180 [[Guinea (British coin)|guinea]]s.

In the [[United States]], there is an example of this car at [[Larz Anderson Auto Museum]] in [[Brookline, Massachusetts]].

