{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox person |name = Sofía Gatica |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date =1967 |birth_place = [[Argentina]] |birth_name = Sofía Gatica |death_place = |occupation = environmentalist |children = |spouse = |nationality =Argentine |awards = [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] |signature = }}
'''Sofía Gatica''' (1976) is an Argentine environmentalist, whose infant daughter Sofia, died just three days after her birth of kidney failure, which is likely caused by pesticide exposure.<ref>[http://www.goldmanprize.org/blog/one-womans-fight-against-glyphosate/ One Woman’s Fight Against Glyphosate]</ref> She was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2012, for her fight against use of toxic pesticides used in agriculture in Argentina, in particular agents containing [[glyphosate]] and [[endosulfan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/recipient/sofia-gatica |title=Sofia Gatica |publisher=[[Goldman Environmental Prize]]|accessdate=31 May 2012}}</ref> In November 2013 she was threatened with death at gunpoint and beaten by unidentified men.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sofía Gatica denunció que fue golpeada|url=http://www.lavoz.com.ar/politica/sofia-gatica-denuncio-que-fue-golpeada|accessdate=6 December 2013|newspaper=La Voz|date=23 November 2013}}</ref><ref>[http://www.enredando.org.ar/2015/09/12/monsanto-nuevamente-golpeo-y-amenazo-a-sofia-gatica/ “Monsanto nuevamente golpeó y amenazó a Sofía Gatica”]</ref>
